Name: FieldSelection

Details:

Categories: Language

Syntax: `$Exp$ . $Name$`

Types:
|`$Exp$`                                | `$Exp$ . $Name$` |
|:--------------------------------------|:-----------------|
| `rel[$T_1$ $L_1$, $T_2$ $L_2$, ... ]` | `set[$T_i$]`     |


Function:

Synopsis:

Description: $Exp$ should evaluate to a relation that has an $i$-th field label $L_i$ that is identical to $Name$.
Return a set with all values of that field.
$Name$ stands for itself and is not evaluated.

Examples:
<screen>
rel[str street, int nm] R = {<"abc", 1>, <"abc", 2>, <"def", 4>, <"def", 5>};
R.street;
</screen>

